},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s64_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"40ed22",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Acne"
]
},
" is a chronic inflammatory skin condition characterized by open and closed comedones (blackheads and whiteheads, respectively) and inflammatory papules, pustules, or nodules."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5bf030",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Rosacea"
]
},
" is a chronic inflammatory skin disorder that affects the cheeks and nose and usually occurs after the age of 30 years. Rosacea has a variety of clinical presentations, including erythrotelangiectatic and papulopustular. The papulopustular variant of rosacea can be confused with acne, but rosacea does not present with comedonal lesions. Telangiectasias and flushing are seen in the erythrotelangiectatic subtype."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ce9e44",
"children":[
"In early stages, rosacea can resemble the malar rash of ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"systemic lupus erythematosus",
"children":[
"SLE"
]
},
"."
]
},
" However, the rash of SLE spares the nasolabial folds. ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"The development of papules, pustules, and flushing is inconsistent with SLE and supports the diagnosis of rosacea."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"3",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_f24"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s64_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"78c700",
"children":[
"The prominent papules and pustules seen in rosacea are not typical of the maculopapular malar rash seen in SLE."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c024c7",
"children":[
"The rash of SLE does not involve the nasolabial folds."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"4",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_f25"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s64_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s64_inline_t2"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f53a56",
"children":[
"All topical retinoids and oral isotretinoin are contraindicated in pregnancy. Topical clindamycin, azelaic acid, and erythromycin are safe in pregnancy."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9661a4",
"children":[
"Treatment of erythrotelangiectatic rosacea focuses primarily on behavioral modifications, such as avoidance of identified triggers of flushing, proper use of sun protection, and use of gentle skin cleansers."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"545c9c",
"children":[
"Treatment for papulopustular rosacea includes topical metronidazole, an azelaic acid formulation, and topical ivermectin. Topical glucocorticoids should be avoided."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7aeeea",
"children":[
"Avoid oral or topical antibiotic monotherapy for treatment of moderate to severe acne because of increased antibiotic resistance; combine with topical benzoyl peroxide."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s64_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"25941b",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"An 18-year-old man has had nodular and cystic acne. Pustules and nodules with scarring are present on the chin, face, back, and chest."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"bfb46d",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose severe inflammatory acne. For treatment, select isotretinoin."
]
}
]
}
]
},
