"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c9d9ec",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Acne (acne vulgaris)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d2790c",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Microcomedones are precursors to acne lesions. They are very common in adolescents but also in preadolescents and adults. Women may have premenstrual flare-ups."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e785aa",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Physical examination: coexisting open and closed comedones, papules, pustules, and nodular lesions located primarily on the face, neck, and upper trunk"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-2 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"497167",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Rosacea"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0199dc",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Not true acne; primary lesion is not a comedone but an inflammatory papule; rhinophyma (bulbous, red nose) is a variant."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"79cf75",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Physical examination: central facial erythema, telangiectasias, papules, and pustules"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-3 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"fc25a8",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Bacterial folliculitis"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0ade6a",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Common in athletes"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ed95e5",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Physical examination: follicular papules; pustules; occasional furuncles on any hair-bearing area, especially scalp, buttocks, and thighs. Most common cause is ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"S. aureus"
]
},
"."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-4 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6a4dba",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Periorificial dermatitis, idiopathic"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"666647",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"More common in women"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8ca8ae",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Physical examination: small (<2 mm) papules and pustules around the mouth or eyelids; similar to acne but without comedones"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-5 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b2dfc3",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Periorificial dermatitis, iatrogenic"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b636f1",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Frequent causes are prolonged topical glucocorticoid therapy for atopic dermatitis and inappropriate use of these agents to treat acne. Similar in appearance to idiopathic type. Classically spares the skin around the lips. Differentiation is by history."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
}
]
